  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs required Gradation 3) is accepted given the COU scope limitation to static compression-bending and the existence of separate COUs addressing torsion and fatigue. All QoI comparisons pass quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, relative error < 10%). The modeling framework is judged credible for its intended use. Note: validation results were generated under Ansys Mechanical build 2026-q1-build-7-rc2; the released model of record is 2026-q1-build-7. The assessment team concluded the patch-level difference introduced no material solver changes, and re-execution under the released build was not performed.",
